==English==

=== Etymology ===
Comes from Middle English ''melancolie'', from Late Latin ''melancholia'', from Greek ''melankholi'' , ''melan''-, meaning "black" and ''khol'', meaning "bile." 

=== Noun ===
'''melancholy'''
#Great sadness or depression; gloom.

=== Adjective ===
'''melancholy'''
#Affected with great sadness or depression.

